description.narrative: (Egypt): The local scholarships program at public universities will: (1) provide 545 scholarships to financially disadvantaged young public school graduates including people with disabilities to pursue programs in fee-based sections at public universities; (2) increase the English language proficiency of students to enable them to compete in the employment market; (3) nurture the students' leadership, cognitive and social skills to contribute to their holistic character development as employable individuals; (4) provide career services to help students secure employment; and (5) foster the links between public universities and the private sector, to ensure undergraduate programming meets the needs of the Egyptian labor market. Graduates will enter the Egyptian workforce able to contribute directly to the growth of the economy through professional positions in existing institutions, or through starting their own businesses that, where successful, will employ other Egyptians.
